[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927019&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927019&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I think your second suggestion (try to validate, and return stale data
if validation failed) is much better than the current scheme.  Of
course, you should sent out the stale RR with a TTL of 0.  I disagree
that there should ever be a time-to-trash, since that will just bring
back the current misery of TTLs.  Instead, the way records get deleted
is that an authoritative reply replaces records, which will make any
previously obsolete records for the same query go away.

